t is covered. If that's the case, should both calls be marked for coverage? It feels like this could affect how I track the coverage accurately. I need to clarify this situation further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gTEayQZdmFq89kYbPPhAM5Tq|fc_08b5f8f1edc1b45a0169fbfb95f8e481929f35b9b9f3f4a36c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/build/test-results/test -name '*DRBG*' -o -name 'TEST-*.xml' | grep DRBG || true\nrg \"DRBGTest|defaultSecureRandom\" tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/build/test-results tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/build/reports/tests -n || true", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 8834, "output": 861, "cacheRead": 48128, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57823, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778121608607, "responseId": "resp_08b5f8f1edc1b45a0169fbfb89b9dc819280e5b296871b5087"}}
